SOCCER STAR PALMER FOUND GUILTY OF INDECENT ASSAULT . Former England soccer star Carlton Palmer was found guilty on Tuesday of indecently assaulting an 18 - year - old woman while he was out drinking with team mates . Palmer , 31 , had denied putting his hand between the teenager ' s legs and making obscene comments in a crowded bar in the northern English city of Leeds . The Leeds United player was fined 600 pounds ( $ 978 ) and ordered to pay 338 pounds costs . Magistrate David Loy said he had taken into account the impact the conviction could have on Palmer ' s career when setting the fine , but added ; " it was a very unpleasant incident indeed . " Palmer ' s lawyers said he would appeal against the conviction . 
